   <mods:abstract>This treatise presents information about the composer André Caplet (1878-1925) and selected poets whose works he set to music. The primary focus of this document will be the lesser known and performed published songs of Caplet for voice and piano: Chanson d'automne (Autumn Song), Deux Poèmes de Charles Baudelaire (Two Poems of Charles Baudelaire), Dans la Fontaine (In The Fountain), Détresse (Distress), Doux fut le trait (Sweet Was The Arrow), En regardant ces belles fleurs (Looking At These Beautiful Flowers), Hymne à la naissance du matin (Hymn to the Birth of the Morning), Lon lon la, La croix douloureuse (The Painful Cross), La part à Dieu The Part To God), Nuit d'automne (Autumn Night), Paroles à l'absente (Words to the Absent), Prière normande (Prayer from Normandy), and Tu nous souriais (You Were Smiling At Us). This guide will be useful for singers and coaches wishing to study or perform his repertoire. Brief biographical information about the composer and each poet will be included as well as historical information on Caplet's mélodies. Each poem will be transliterated using the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA) and will include a word-for-word English translation in addition to a poetic translation. In addition to these translations, each piece will be evaluated addressing the following elements: voice type, singer expertise, range, tessitura, phrase concerns, rhythmic intricacy, coloratura requirements, poetic complexity, accompaniment issues, dynamic expectations, duration, and stamina to name a few. Availability of commercial recordings will also be provided.</mods:abstract>
